article.headline: Iona 76, St. Francis, Pa. 66
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. (AP) -- Dexter Gray led five Iona players in double figures with 15 points, and the Gaels took control with a 12-0 run to start the second half in a 76-66 win over St. Francis, Pa., on Wednesday. Iona improved to 4-7 under first-year head coach Kevin Willard, doubling its victory total from last season when it went 2-28. St. Francis (3-7) was denied its first four-game winning streak since the 2002-03 season. Iona trailed much of the first half before taking a 35-33 lead into intermission. The Gaels opened the second half with back-to-back 3-pointers by Milan Prodanovic and Kyle Camper to start the game-changing spurt. Iona stretched the lead to 47-33 before the Red Flash scored in the second half. St. Francis got no closer than seven the rest of the way. Camper had 13 points, Prodanovic 12, Devon Clarke 11 and Gary Springer 10 for Iona. Cale Nelson and Chris Berry had 15 points apiece to lead St. Francis.
